Iterable<LFEdge>, Collection<LFEdge>, Set<LFEdge>
public class FilteredLFEdgeSet
extends FilteredSet<LFEdge>

A filtered set of LF edges. This class extends FilteredSet to provide the additional functionality of edge-based views of its contents: sourceView(), targetView(), and labelView(), which respectively get the set of source vertices, set of target vertices, and set of labels contained in the edges in this set. All of these view sets are read-only, so that attempting to add or remove elements from them (including via the iterator) throws UnsupportedOperationException.

Author:
Scott Martin

sourceView

public Collection<LFVertex> sourceView()
Gets a view of this filtered edge set as a set of LF vertices that are the source vertices for each edge in this set.

Returns:
A set containing every LF vertex that is the source vertex of some edge in this set. Note that the returned collection is immutable, and may contain duplicate vertices.

labelView

public Collection<LFEdgeLabel> labelView()
Gets a view of this filtered edge set as a set of LF vertices that are the labels for each edge in this set.

Returns:
